                            <comment id="17416477" author="karmagyz" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2021 06:23:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=wangyang0918&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;wangyang0918&quot;&gt;wangyang0918&lt;/a&gt; I think we can add a retry logic in building the watcher and throw a fatal error if the watcher cannot be rebuilt. Could you assign this to me?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17416493" author="ouyangwuli" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2021 06:54:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=guoyangze&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;guoyangze&quot;&gt;guoyangze&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&#160;Can we configure parameters &#8216;kubernetes.watch.reconnectInterval&#8217; and &#8216;kubernetes.watch.reconnectLimit&#8217; to fix this problem &#65311;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17416500" author="karmagyz" created="Fri, 17 Sep 2021 07:15:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the information, I think we can leverage &#8216;kubernetes.watch.reconnectInterval&#8217; and &#8216;kubernetes.watch.reconnectLimit&#8217; to implement the retry logic. However, the key point of this issue is that we need to handle the failure of rebuilding the watcher.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17417043" author="fly_in_gis" created="Sat, 18 Sep 2021 06:31:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we need to retry in the &lt;tt&gt;FlinkKubeClient#watchPodsAndDoCallback&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
